SIMPLE: limitary
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Limitary
<hw>Lim"i*ta*ry</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧m"⟦icr⟧*t⟦asl⟧*r⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>limitaris</ets>. See <er>Limit</er> ,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Placed at the limit, as a
guard.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Proud <xex>limitary</xex> cherub.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Confined within limits; limited in extent,
authority, power, etc.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>limitary</xex>
ocean.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Trench.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The poor, <qex>limitary</qex> creature calling himself a man of
the world.</q> <rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Limiting, or tending to limit;
restrictive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Doctrines <qex>limitary</qex>, if not subversive of the papal
power.</q> <rj><qau>Milman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Limitary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Limitary
<hw>Lim"i*ta*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>limitaries</plw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧m"⟦icr⟧*t⟦asl⟧*r⟦icr⟧z)</pr>.</plu>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>That which serves to limit; a boundary; border
land.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A limiter. See <er>Limiter</er>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Limitate</ent>⟦br⟧
